---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout 
  title="FAQ – Cybersecurity Kits for Small Business | SMBCyberHub" 
  description="Get answers to frequently asked questions about SMBCyberHub kits, cybersecurity training, licensing, insurance compliance, and more."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={`
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "1. Why not just use free cybersecurity templates online?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Most free templates are generic, outdated, or overly technical — and few are aligned with GDPR or ISO27001. SMBCyberHub kits are purpose-built for SMBs and designed to be clear, printable, and audit-friendly."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "2. Do I need IT experience to use these kits?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Not at all. Each kit is built for office managers, team leads, and founders — no technical jargon, no setup headaches. If you can onboard a new hire, you can deploy our materials."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "3. Are these kits really audit-ready?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. The policies and training content are mapped to key compliance standards like GDPR Article 39.1(b) and ISO27001 Clause 7.2.2. You also get templates for training logs, sign-offs, and breach notifications to help with insurer, client, or auditor requests."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "4. Is this a subscription?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "No. Each kit is a one-time purchase. You’ll get an instant download, offline access, and full internal-use rights forever — no recurring fees, no upsells, no login required."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "5. Can I preview the content before buying?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. A free sample kit is available directly from the homepage. It includes a training slide, checklist, and part of a policy so you can see the clarity and formatting before committing."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "6. What if I have a team larger than 20 people?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "If you’re an agency, MSP, or need licensing for multiple clients or teams, the Agency Kit (coming soon) includes editable versions and a multi-client license."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "7. Do you offer refunds?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Due to the nature of digital products, all sales are final. However, we provide a free sample kit to help you evaluate fit before purchasing."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "8. Can I use this for insurance or client due diligence?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Absolutely. Many buyers use SMBCyberHub kits to meet cyber insurance requirements or respond to security questionnaires from clients. The kits include documentation logs, staff quiz sign-offs, and breach notification templates — all helpful during onboarding, audits, or risk assessments."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  `}></script>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-800">

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">1. Why not just use free cybersecurity templates online?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Most free templates are generic, outdated, or overly technical — and few are aligned with GDPR or ISO27001. SMBCyberHub kits are purpose-built for SMBs and designed to be clear, printable, and audit-friendly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">2. Do I need IT experience to use these kits?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Not at all. Each kit is built for office managers, team leads, and founders — no technical jargon, no setup headaches. If you can onboard a new hire, you can deploy our materials.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">3. Are these kits really audit-ready?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Yes. The policies and training content are mapped to key compliance standards like GDPR Article 39.1(b) and ISO27001 Clause 7.2.2. You also get templates for training logs, sign-offs, and breach notifications to help with insurer, client, or auditor requests.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">4. Is this a subscription?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          No. Each kit is a one-time purchase. You’ll get an instant download, offline access, and full internal-use rights forever — no recurring fees, no upsells, no login required.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">5. Can I preview the content before buying?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Yes. A free sample kit is available directly from the homepage. It includes a training slide, checklist, and part of a policy so you can see the clarity and formatting before committing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">6. What if I have a team larger than 20 people?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          If you’re an agency, MSP, or need licensing for multiple clients or teams, the <strong>Agency Kit</strong> (coming soon) includes editable versions and a multi-client license.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">7. Do you offer refunds?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Due to the nature of digital products, all sales are final. However, we provide a free sample kit to help you evaluate fit before purchasing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">8. Can I use this for insurance or client due diligence?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Absolutely. Many buyers use SMBCyberHub kits to meet cyber insurance requirements or respond to security questionnaires from clients. The kits include documentation logs, staff quiz sign-offs, and breach notification templates — all helpful during onboarding, audits, or risk assessments.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
